-- Volcker Says U.S. Doesn’t Need 6 Financial Regulatory Agencies
-- B y   J o h n   D e t r i x h e
-- 2013-05-29T17:05:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-29/volcker-says-u-s-doesn-t-need-6-financial-regulatory-agencies.html
Former Federal Reserve Chairman  Paul
Volcker  said today the U.S. “does not need six financial
regulatory agencies.”  “It is a recipe for indecision, for neglect and stalemate,
adding up to ineffectiveness,'' Volcker said, speaking to the
Economic Club of New York. ‘‘The time has come for change.’’  To contact the reporter on this story:
